184
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:57,800
stain, but the end of the week is a very, very useful phrase because it means that maybe
因为我们通常把周末想成周五，也许是周四、周五。

185
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:03,840
today's Monday or Tuesday, by Friday or Saturday, we'll have this ready for you.
所以我可以说是“周末前”或“今天结束前”。

186
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:07,480
Because we think of the end of the week as Friday, maybe Thursday, Friday.
没错。

187
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:11,120
So I can say the end of the week or the end of the day.
“月底前”。

188
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:12,120
Exactly.
或者“年底前”。

189
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,120
The end of the month.
没错。

190
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,120
Or the end of the year.
所以“...结束前”通常指的是最后的时间点。

191
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,120
Exactly.
所以谢天谢地，这周结束了。

192
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:20,640
So the end of is usually the last time.
我准备好过周末了。

193
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:23,840
So thank goodness it's the end of the week.
非常好。

194
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:25,640
I'm ready for my weekend.
好的。

195
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:26,640
Very good.
那里也有很棒的短语。

196
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:27,640
Okay.
让我们最后听一遍对话。

197
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:29,080
So great phrases there as well.
谢天谢地你还开着门。

198
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:32,080
Let's listen to the dialogue for the last time.
我有急事。

199
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:41,080
Thank God you are open.
谢天谢地你还开着门。

200
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,080
I have an emergency.
我有急事。

201
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,080
Hello Mr. Henderson.
你好，亨德森先生。

202
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:44,080
What can I do for you?
我能为您做些什么？

203
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:49,080
I need this dress and this suit dry cleaned ASAP.
我需要尽快干洗这条裙子和这套西装。

204
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:50,080
Okay.
好的。

205
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:52,080
I can have it ready by the end of the week.
我可以在周末前准备好。

206
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:54,080
No, you don't understand.
不，你没明白。

207
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:55,960
I need this tomorrow morning.
我明天早上就要。

208
00:07:55,960 --> 00:08:01,720
I accidentally spilled beer all over my wife's dress and we have a wedding to attend tomorrow.
我不小心把啤酒洒在我妻子的裙子上，我们明天要参加一个婚礼。

209
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,080
She's going to kill me.
她会杀了我的。

210
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:04,080
Okay.
好的。

211
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:07,680
I can have it ready tomorrow afternoon, but this suit is also very stained.
我可以在明天下午准备好，但这套西装也沾了很多污渍。

212
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:10,080
I can't guarantee we can remove it completely.
我不能保证能完全去除。

213
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:11,080
Fine.
好吧。

214
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:13,920
Can you also iron and starch this shirt?
你能顺便熨烫并上浆这件衬衫吗？

215
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:14,920
Certainly.
当然可以。

216
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:15,920
Great.
太好了。

217
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:16,920
This is our secret.
这是我们之间的秘密。

218
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:26,080
If you see my wife, say nothing to her about this.
如果你见到我妻子，什么都别说。

219
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,080
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

220
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:29,040
So now dry cleaning, ironing.
所以现在聊干洗、熨烫。

221
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:32,200
Are you good at this or do you get a lot of your clothes dry cleaned?
你擅长这个吗，还是你经常把衣服送去干洗？

222
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,480
I'm pretty good at this actually.
其实我挺擅长的。

223
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,920
I don't like to wash clothes.
我不喜欢洗衣服。

224
00:08:34,920 --> 00:08:38,880
I get really bored with the washing machine, but I actually really like ironing.
用洗衣机洗衣服让我觉得很无聊，但我其实很喜欢熨烫。

225
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:39,880
Really?
真的吗？

226
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:40,880
Yeah.
是啊。

227
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:41,880
I find it very relaxing.
我觉得熨烫很放松。

228
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:42,880
Really?
真的吗？

229
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:44,160
I find it very frustrating.
我觉得熨烫很让人沮丧。

230
00:08:44,160 --> 00:08:45,160
Really?
真的吗？

231
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:46,160
Why is that?
为什么？

232
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:52,440
Because I can't really iron well because I start on one side and I'm getting all the
因为我熨得不好，我从一边开始把所有的

233
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:57,760
lines out and then the other side gets wrinkled or lines appear where I don't want them to
褶皱弄平，然后另一边又起皱，或者出现我不想有的

234
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:58,760
appear.
褶皱。

235
00:08:58,760 --> 00:08:59,760
It's very frustrating for me.
这让我很沮丧。

236
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:00,760
It is frustrating.
确实让人沮丧。

237
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:01,840
It takes some practice.
这需要一些练习。

238
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:05,320
My suggestion is to use the spritzer.
我的建议是使用喷雾器。

239
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:09,240
In the iron, there's some water that can come out like that.
熨斗里有一些水可以像那样喷出来。

240
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:16,240
Well, if you spray the water, it makes the lines go out for longer.
嗯，如果你喷水，可以让褶皱消失得更久。

241
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:18,960
Because if you iron over that, it's more permanent.
因为如果你熨烫过那个地方，它会变得更持久。

242
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:23,400
I've also seen some sprays sometimes that you can spray your clothes with some special
我还见过一些喷雾，有时你可以用它们喷在衣服上，喷上一些特殊的

243
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:27,360
chemical that's not actually starch, but it helps remove the wrinkles quicker.
化学物质，其实不是淀粉，但能帮助更快地去除皱纹。

244
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:28,360
Exactly.
没错。

245
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,360
I don't use that.
我不用那个。

246
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,440
I use water generally, but they're all available.
我一般用水，但它们都有卖的。

247
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,480
All right.
好了。

248
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:34,400
So that's all the time we have for today.
这就是我们今天的所有时间了。

249
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:39,880
If you have any questions or comments, you can visit our comment section on EnglishPod.com
如果你有任何问题或评论，可以访问我们EnglishPod.com的评论区，

250
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:41,040
and we'll see you guys there.
我们会在那里见你们。

251
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,040
Bye, everyone.
大家再见。

252
00:09:42,040 --> 00:10:10,340
Bye.
再见。
